# Install guides for my computers

## Arch linux

- follow installation from: https://itsfoss.com/install-arch-linux/ and https://wiki.archlinux.org/index.php/installation_guide
- create 4 partitions:
	- efi with 512M (EFI System)
	- root with 64GB (Linux root x86_64)
	- swap with 16GB (Linux swap)
	- home with rest (Linux home)
- pacstrap /mnt base base-devel linux linux-firmware vim nano vi
- add a user
- install terminator
- install gnome and i3

## General dependencies

* update and upgrade everything
* install terminator and guake
* create an ssh key (ssh-keygen -t rsa) and add to GitHub.
* install firefox bookmarks as well as firefox addons
* install git and add 'github/dotfiles' and copy relevent dotfiles
* install zsh and zpretzo and add .zshrc and .zpreztorc (https://github.com/sorin-ionescu/prezto)
* install neovim, add "nvim/init.vim" and install Vundle (git clone https://github.com/VundleVim/Vundle.vim.git ~/.config/nvim/bundle/Vundle.vim) using PluginInstall
* install i3, i3-wm and add configs from dotfiles (help: https://i3wm.org/docs/userguide.html)
* add .condarc and conda install environment called 'default'
```bash
~/miniconda3/bin/conda create -n default python=3.*
```
* install atom and add keymap
* Install software, such as
  - pycharm/webstorm/clion (add settings from dropbox), sublime
  - install texlive
  - install R from source and openblas
  - rstudio
  - skype, telegram, signal
  - firefox, thunderbird,
  - cuda and nvidia driver
  - pcmanfm and audacious
  - install redshift
  - feh, 'light' (https://github.com/haikarainen/light)
* clone my repositories using SSH
* smaller things:
	- customize arch/ubuntu using gnome tweak utils (remove window borders, etc.)GG
